action: optimize
reasoning: "Q3 is 16.9x slower than DuckDB (critical bottleneck) and Q6 is 8.6x slower - both have clear, high-impact optimizations available. Zone maps on sorted data are proven low-risk techniques with 3-12x speedup potential. With 2 iterations remaining, we can aggressively pursue these optimizations."
selected_recommendations[4]: 0,2,3,1
focus_areas[4]: Zone map block skipping for Q6 (8-12x speedup expected),Zone map block skipping for Q3 tables (3-5x speedup expected),Partitioned parallel hash join for Q3 (2-3x additional speedup),SIMD vectorized filtering for Q6 (2-3x additional speedup after zone maps)
strategy_notes: "Aggressive attack on Q3 and Q6 performance gaps. Zone maps are the highest ROI since data is already sorted. Combined optimizations should bring Q6 to 4-10ms (DuckDB parity) and Q3 to 90-150ms (approaching DuckDB's 80ms). Q1 is already competitive at 74ms vs DuckDB's 84ms, so defer Q1 optimizations to iteration 2-3 if needed. Focus on proven, low-risk techniques first (zone maps) with one medium-risk addition (partitioned join) to maximize Q3 improvement."
notes: "Implementation order: (1) Zone maps for Q6 first - simplest case, immediate validation. (2) Zone maps for Q3 - three tables but same pattern. (3) SIMD for Q6 - builds on zone map pruning. (4) Partitioned join for Q3 - most complex, highest risk. If time pressure, prioritize recommendations 0,2,3 and defer 1 to next iteration."